SIMPLE: overrule
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Overrule
<hw>O`ver*rule"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Overruled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Overruling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To rule
over; to govern or determine by superior authority.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To rule or determine in a contrary way; to decide
against; to abrogate or alter; <as>as, God <ex>overrules</ex> the
purposes of men; the chairman <ex>overruled</ex> the point of
order.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His passion and animosity <qex>overruled</qex> his conscience.</q>
<rj><qau>Clarendon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>These [difficulties] I had habitually <qex>overruled</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>F. W. Newman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>To supersede, reject, annul, or
rule against; <as>as, the plea, or the decision, was <ex>overruled</ex>
by the court</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overrule</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Overrule
<hw>O`ver*rule"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To be superior or supreme in
ruling or controlling; <as>as, God rules and
<ex>overrules</ex></as>.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overruler</ent>⟦br⟧
